ation of novel, still untested filmmaking technologies could perhaps contribute to the financial, critical, and cultural success of the movie in which those new technologies were utilized.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"gp.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID8"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID11","SecondaryAttribute":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking technologies contributes to the financial, critical, and cultural success of the cinematic production in which those new technologies were utilized.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"sd.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID11"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID151","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor ga...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. <br><br>The professor gave this message.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor ga...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with a real-world case study.","DataExportTag":"Q151","QuestionID":"QID151"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID134","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with this real-world case study:","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with a real-world case study.","DataExportTag":"Q134","QuestionID":"QID134"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID167","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with the following message.","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor gave the following message.","DataExportTag":"Q167","QuestionID":"QID167"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID83","SecondaryAttribute":"The information you were shown derives from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof f...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>The information you were shown derives from this case study:<br><\/i><br><b>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>The company came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found instantaneous results: shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q83","QuestionID":"QID83","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The information you were shown derives from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof f...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID2","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case: Companies that package their pr...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"hypothetical","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case: Companies that package their pr...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID2"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID160","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. Please read it...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. <u>Please read it closely.<\/u><\/b><u><br><\/u><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. Please read it...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q160","QuestionID":"QID160"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID132","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. Please read it...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. <u>Please read it closely.<\/u><\/b><br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q132","QuestionID":"QID132","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. Please read it...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID143","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was: Companies that package their pr...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"color:#27ae60;\"><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was: Companies that package their pr...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q143","QuestionID":"QID143"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID176","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q176","QuestionID":"QID176"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID200","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q200","QuestionID":"QID200"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID97","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent could someone apply this information to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent could someone apply this information to other situations?","DataExportTag":"Q97","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent could someone apply this information to other situations?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 1"},"2":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 2"},"3":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 3"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID97"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_1SRJEJ9F6HEN2w6","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID28","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"gp.a","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to ot