 University, about explanations and understanding. The amount of time that we expect this task should take you is indicated in the description of this HIT. There are no known risks to participation in this study, and there are no benefits to participants. You will be compensated for your participation according to the description of this HIT, based on the amount of time this HIT is expected to take. Your participation in this study is voluntary, and you may choose not to participate now or to stop participating at any time. Your responses will be stored securely and only research personnel and those responsible for supervising our research will have access to them. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact the researchers at cognition.development@yale.edu.","DataExportTag":"Q1","QuestionID":"QID1717457503"}}]}